<doc id="772546" wikidata="Q7337033" url="?curid=772546" title="RiverCentre">
<text>The Saint Paul RiverCentre is a convention center located in Saint Paul, Minnesota. It sits adjacent to the Roy Wilkins Auditorium, Xcel Energy Center and the Ordway Center for the Performing Arts.

The convention center opened in 1998. It was designed by Hammel Green and Abrahamson, Inc.

It has twice been honored as &quot;Best Convention Center&quot; by Minnesota Meetings and Events Magazine. It hosts a large variety of events and has been the home of the annual Festival of Nations.

